  "body": "We have a Git Convention section in the Developer Guide docs for helm, which gives the basic outline of the process for working on and submitting a change. While our Contributing doc does mention the fact that we require you to sign the code (and lots of detail on how to do this), it would be helpful just to mention it as part of the Developer Guide outline, e.g. where it currently says:\r\n\r\n\"When you are ready for us to review, push your branch to GitHub, and then open a new pull request with us.\"\r\n\r\n...perhaps we might say:\r\n\r\n\"When you are ready for us to review, sign your commit, push your branch to GitHub, and then open a new pull request with us.\"\r\n\r\n",
